Johannesburg

<img data-attachment-id="6120" data-permalink="https://www.newframe.com/durban-the-city-that-forces-the-poor-to-defecate-in-the-streets/jhb-stats/" data-orig-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS.png" data-orig-size="481,202" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="JHB STATS" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS-300x126.png" data-large-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS.png" src="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS.png" alt="" class="wp-image-6120" srcset="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS.png 481w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS-300x126.png 300w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/JHB-STATS-480x202.png 480w" sizes="(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px" />

City of Johannesburg officials appear to have misunderstood the focus and instead supplied information relating to toilets in shack settlements.
The city has 7 178 chemical toilets, 55 311 pit latrines and 20 communal ablution blocks, they say, which provide basic sanitation services in these areas. 
The annual budget for chemical toilets is R72 million and R28 million to empty the pit latrines. 
City officials could not say how many toilets have been built since the advent of democracy.


